How to Write a Good Prompt for Einstein Segments in Data Cloud

When creating a segment, use certain formats and language to get the best results possible. Provide descriptive names for data model objects (DMOs) and attributes to ensure that generative AI can understand them. OpenAI was trained on data that leans toward the United States, which influences Einstein’s responses. If you require a specific country, enter the name of the country in the prompt.

Available with add-on license: Segmentation and Activation
Writing Good Prompts

Here are some examples to help you improve your results. The generative AI model isn’t always consistent when answering requests, so you might get different results when entering the same prompt.

BEST PRACTICE	NOT RECOMMENDED PROMPT	RECOMMENDED PROMPT
Use custom field names in the prompt.	Create a segment of all Northern Trail Customers	Create a segment of all Brand="Northern Trail" customers
Make the prompt specific, not general.	Customers who live in the UK	Customers who live in the UK who engaged with my product in the past 60 days
When requesting brand data, specify it.	Customers who engaged with my website	Customers who engaged with the website "mywebsite.com"
Use “and” instead of commas.	Customers who like running, cycling, swimming	Customers who like running and cycling and swimming
Don’t use one-word prompts.	Fishermen	Customers who enjoy fishing
Be explicit, not implicit.	Top customers	10% highest paying customers
Avoid complex date filters	Customers with cases closed in the last week of every month	Customers with cases that closed this past month
Supported Operators

When you write a prompt, enter accurate descriptive text. Use these operators to specify information. When writing prompts, you can’t use the OR and Exclude operators.

Text

Equal
Not Equal
In
Not In
Has Value
Has No Value

Numbers

Equal
Not Equal
Less Than
Less Than Or Equal
Greater Than
Greater Than Or Equal
Between
Has Value
Has No Value
Is Not Between

Dates

Is Anniversary Of
Is Not Anniversary Of
Day Of Month
Is Yesterday
Is Today
Is Tomorrow
Before Day Of Month
After Day Of Month
Not Day Of Month
Day of Week
Equal
Between
Month Of Year
